description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced Nurse Practitioner to join the team here at Dunelm Medical Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity for an experienced Nurse Practitioner with a proven track record looking for their next challenge in Primary Care. If this is you, we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for someone who can work seamlessly between our medical and nursing teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to undertake full time hours by working either a 4 or 5 day week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a well-established training Practice based across the City of Durham with premises in Bearpark, Framwellgate Moor and Gilesgate. Our combined list size is currently 13,650 across three sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly, innovative and supportive practice with a strong emphasis on work / life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Being consistently high achieving in QOF.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Being SystmOne including Ardens, Accurx and MJOG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having regular clinical meetings and Protected Learning Time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having a Good CQC rating with Outstanding for our treatment of vulnerable people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modern premises.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proactive, collaborative working with our Federation, Primary Care Network and other partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
